o-empty rule\n- 3744 tests pass, 96.97% coverage, all 156 files above 80% floor\n\n### 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests — verification (2026-03-25T01:44:00Z)\n\n- Unit-testable verification — no Docker required\n- All 6 ACs passed with direct CLI evidence\n- Proof format required adjustment: parser needs `\\`\\`\\`bash` + `\\`\\`\\`output` pairs and `**Tier:** unit-testable` (not `**Verification tier:**`)\n- Beads sync failed (bd CLI not installed) — non-blocking\n\n### 14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T01:45:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `docker ps` returns \"Cannot connect to the Docker daemon\"\n- Both verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-5→6, 14-6→5.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 15-3-template-migration-static-files — create-story (2026-03-25T01:46:00Z)\n\n- Story file already existed with full content and correct verification tags. No creation needed.\n- Risk: Story touches 18+ files — large migration may exceed session time budget.\n- Risk: AC3 only tests Dockerfile.nodejs equivalence explicitly. Other templates lack explicit equivalence ACs.\n- Risk: `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` migration ambiguity unresolved (template vs code generation).\n\n### 15-3-template-migration-static-files — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:00:00Z)\n\n- Test mock fragility: Three test files mock `node:fs` globally, breaking `renderTemplateFile`. Fixed by providing mock via `vi.importActual`. Recurring pattern risk for future tests.\n- verify-prompt.ts and showboat-template.ts not migrated: Complex TypeScript logic (conditionals, loops, computed values) cannot be expressed as `{{VAR}}` interpolation. Left as TS generators.\n- Dual template content for Dockerfiles eliminated: Stack providers and dockerfile-template.ts both now delegate to static files.\n- 3775/3775 tests pass. Build succeeds.\n","numLines":249,"startLine":1,"totalLines":249}}}
