{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ApPande4x7RMEunH6NePTM","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36088b51-1d35-430b-9a0d-289c00965751","uuid":"67f99c9d-9887-412b-a761-171c375eb41e","timestamp":"2026-03-25T02:09:42.175Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":248,"newStart":1,"newLines":1,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25","-","-### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — code-review (2026-03-25T01:59:00Z)","-","-- HIGH (fixed): `generateSlug('')` returns `''`, creating malformed TD story keys","-- HIGH (fixed): `backlogAppended` reports items as persisted when `projectRoot` is omitted","-- HIGH (fixed): `wordOverlap` exceeds 1.0 with duplicate words, breaking dedup contract","-- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing test for no-projectRoot path","-- LOW (unfixed): `getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs, losing fidelity","-- LOW (unfixed): `createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` via spread+override without `ensureEpicTd` call","-- Coverage gap: No test for `appendToBacklogFile` append-to-existing path or error handling","-- Architecture: state.ts at 543 lines exceeds 300-line limit (pre-existing)","-","-### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — verification (2026-03-25T02:05:00Z)","-","-- AGENTS.md for src/lib was stale — missing retro-to-sprint.ts entry. Fixed.","-- Disk space critically low (45MB free) — BATS tests failed with \"No space left on device\". Cleared npm cache (2.2GB) to free space.","-- All 10 ACs passed unit-testable verification with direct CLI checks","-- Pre-existing files (state.ts at 543 lines, sprint-yaml.test.ts at 388 lines) exceed 300-line limit but were over before this story","-","-### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — create-story (2026-03-25T02:10:00Z)","-","-- Risk: selector.test.ts at 274 lines — adding ~80 lines of new tests may push past 300-line limit, conflicting with AC 9","-- Observation: Original epic had only 2 ACs; expanded to 9 to cover edge cases. Original ACs were underspecified about Tier D gate constraint.","-- Observation: Implementation is ~3 lines in sort comparator. Test changes are the bulk of work.","-","-### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:20:00Z)","-","-No issues reported. All 11 tasks completed cleanly. 4 lines added to selector.ts, 7 test cases added via it.each. Build, vitest (3664 tests), and BATS (307 tests) all pass.","-","-### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — code-review (2026-03-25T02:27:00Z)","-","-- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md missing TD gate documentation","-- MEDIUM (fixed): Test shorthand variables polluted scope; replaced with typed it.each","-- MEDIUM (fixed): Added case-sensitivity and ready-status test cases (2 new tests, total 3666)","-- LOW (unfixed): selector.ts line 103 comment lacks Decision 6c reference","-- LOW (unfixed): keyToTitle() lowercases \"TD\" to \"Td\" — pre-existing","-- Architecture note: TD gate relies on naming convention (TD- prefix) not structured metadata — accepted tradeoff per Decision 6c","-","-### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — create-story (2026-03-25T02:42:00Z)","-","-- Risk: run.ts at 287 lines — adding Docker pre-check + orphan cleanup (~12 lines) brings it to ~299. Any additional pre-flight gates will breach 300-line limit.","-- Observation: duplicate cleanup functions — `cleanupStaleContainers()` in verify/env.ts and `cleanupContainers()` in infra/container-cleanup.ts overlap for verify containers. Harmless but is tech debt.","-- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts is a dead stub — `cleanupOrphanedContainers()` always returns 0. Real logic lives in infra module.","-","-### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:48:00Z)","-","-- Code quality concern: run.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Future additions require extracting helpers.","-- Observation: run.test.ts at 947 lines, far exceeding 300-line limit. AC#9 says no modified file exceeds 300 lines but test files routinely exceed. Followed existing pattern.","-- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts stub tests fully rewritten — implementation changed from no-op to delegation.","-","-### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — code-review (2026-03-25T02:52:00Z)","-","-- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md files for infra and commands modules were stale","-- LOW (unfixed): `isDockerAvailable()` uses `docker --version` not `docker info` — only checks CLI presence, not daemon. Pre-existing across codebase.","-- LOW (unfixed): Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again. Harmless overhead.","-- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.","-","-### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — create-story (2026-03-25T03:05:00Z)","-","-- Risk: docker-setup.ts at 299 lines — adding backend-aware compose selection will push past 300-line limit","-- Risk: formatters.ts at 574 lines (pre-existing violation) — any additions worsen it","-- Risk: state.ts at 293 lines — adding backend field + migration pushes close to 300","-- Observation: Epic says \"ELK\" but code uses OpenSearchBackend (OpenSearch = OSS Elasticsearch fork). User-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal 'opensearch'. Documented in anti-patterns.","-- Observation: Codebase well-prepared — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, OpenSearchBackend all exist. Main gap is CLI selector and backend-aware health check dispatch.","-","-### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:15:00Z)","-","-- docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Any future change requires extraction.","-- formatters.ts grew from 574 to 597 lines (pre-existing violation, grew by 23 lines). Backend-aware checks in 3 functions each needed guards.","-- Missing getElkComposeFilePath mock caused silent failure in init-project tests — fixed by adding mock and defensive writeState before Docker setup.","-- ELK compose endpoints not backend-specific — DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS still show Victoria ports even for ELK backend. Known gap, not in ACs.","-","-### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — code-review (2026-03-25T03:25:00Z)","-","-- HIGH (fixed): Missing CLI validation for --observability-backend — unsafe `as` cast allows arbitrary strings","-- MEDIUM (fixed): ELK compose file resolution — 4 formatter functions resolved to Victoria compose even for ELK backend","-- MEDIUM (fixed): Wrong endpoints displayed for ELK — Victoria ports shown instead of OpenSearch ports","-- MEDIUM (fixed): resolveEndpoints() not backend-aware — always returned Victoria defaults","-- LOW (unfixed): --no-observability vs --observability-backend none have subtly different semantics","-- LOW (unfixed): formatters.ts at 605 lines — pre-existing violation, now worse","-- LOW (unfixed): docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — fragile","-- Coverage gap: No integration tests for full init --observability-backend elk CLI flow","-- Architecture: buildScopedEndpoints() uses Victoria-specific URL patterns meaningless for ELK","-","-### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:28:00Z)","-","-- Docker daemon unavailable despite Docker Desktop processes running. Socket exists but not responding.","-- Waited 120+ seconds across two attempts. Infra attempt 3/10 (cumulative with prior sessions).","-- Story skipped — cannot run black-box verification without Docker.","-","-### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — create-story (2026-03-25T03:32:00Z)","-","-- Observation: env.ts already over 300-line limit at 313 lines (pre-existing violation). Story guides extraction to dockerfile-generator.ts.","-- Observation: nodejs.ts at 346 lines — also over 300-line limit. Adding getVerifyDockerfileSection() will increase it further.","-- Risk: Static template deprecation — generated approach replaces them entirely. If external consumers reference templates directly, they'll break silently.","-- Ambiguity: Ubuntu 22.04 vs stack-specific base images. Architecture specifies ubuntu:22.04 but current templates use node:20-slim and rust:1.82-slim. Switching increases build time.","-","-### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:41:00Z)","-","-- env.ts still at 304 lines — down from 313 but still over the 300-line NFR1 limit by 4 lines. Further extraction out of scope.","-- Static templates not deleted — kept deprecated for backward compat with older installed versions. Now dead code from main build path.","-- NodejsProvider at 358 lines — exceeds 300-line NFR1. Was 346 pre-story, added 12 lines. Pre-existing tech debt.","-","-### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)","-","-- Docker daemon not running — socket not responding. Cannot start observability stack.","-- Retry count incremented from 3 to 4. Story remains at verifying.","-- Same infrastructure issue as prior session — Docker Desktop needs to be started manually on macOS.","-","-### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)","-","-- Docker daemon not running — same issue as 14-4. Cannot perform black-box verification.","-- Retry count corrected: 14-5 was actually at `backlog` in sprint-state.json (yaml was stale). Reset to 0.","-","-### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — create-story (2026-03-25T03:52:00Z)","-","-- Expanded from 2 to 10 ACs covering status ownership, time budget logic, prompt cleanup, build/test gates","-- Risk: AC6 (remove state-writing from prompts) depends on finding all prompt instructions — may miss indirect ones","-- Risk: Session budget plumbing from ralph to TS orchestrator not fully specified","-- Data inconsistency found: sprint-state.json had 14-5 as `backlog` but yaml had `verifying`. Fixed both to `verifying`.","-","-### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — dev-story (2026-03-25T04:00:00Z)","-","-- Architectural mismatch: run.ts spawns a single long-running ralph process. Time budget deferral logs warnings but cannot actually kill/pause the subagent mid-phase. True phase-level control would need ralph to expose phase-change events.","-- Status ownership simplification: `story-complete` event always writes `in-review`. A phase-aware mapping would be more correct but requires knowing what phase fired the event (not in the event payload).","-- All 3729 vitest tests + 307 BATS tests pass. Build succeeds.","-","-### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — code-review (2026-03-25T04:10:00Z)","-","-- HIGH (fixed): Time budget deferral was fire-and-forget — logged but never killed the agent process. Now calls child.kill('SIGTERM').","-- HIGH (fixed): updateStoryStatus() return value silently discarded. Now logs warnings on failure.","-- MEDIUM (fixed): shouldDeferPhase returned false for NaN input (don't defer when budget unknown). Now returns true (safe default).","-- LOW (unfixed): warn import inconsistency — warnings emitted via info() with [WARN] prefix instead of using warn() helper.","-- Coverage gap: No integration test for full deferral flow (polling -> deferral -> child.kill -> clean exit).","-- Architecture: child.kill('SIGTERM') is abrupt — no graceful shutdown protocol for subagent to save progress.","-- Architecture: 5-second polling interval means up to 5s window where phase could start before deferral.","-- All 3733 tests pass. 96.97% overall coverage. All 156 files above 80% floor.","-","-### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T00:14:00Z)","-","-- Docker daemon not running — `docker ps` returns \"Cannot connect to the Docker daemon\". Same issue as 