,"-- Story file already existed with full content and correct verification tags. No creation needed.","-- Risk: Story touches 18+ files — large migration may exceed session time budget.","-- Risk: AC3 only tests Dockerfile.nodejs equivalence explicitly. Other templates lack explicit equivalence ACs.","-- Risk: `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` migration ambiguity unresolved (template vs code generation).","-","-### 15-3-template-migration-static-files — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:00:00Z)","-","-- Test mock fragility: Three test files mock `node:fs` globally, breaking `renderTemplateFile`. Fixed by providing mock via `vi.importActual`. Recurring pattern risk for future tests.","-- verify-prompt.ts and showboat-template.ts not migrated: Complex TypeScript logic (conditionals, loops, computed values) cannot be expressed as `{{VAR}}` interpolation. Left as TS generators.","-- Dual template content for Dockerfiles eliminated: Stack providers and dockerfile-template.ts both now delegate to static files.","-- 3775/3775 tests pass. Build succeeds."]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n\n### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — code-review (2026-03-25T01:59:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): `generateSlug('')` returns `''`, creating malformed TD story keys\n- HIGH (fixed): `backlogAppended` reports items as persisted when `projectRoot` is omitted\n- HIGH (fixed): `wordOverlap` exceeds 1.0 with duplicate words, breaking dedup contract\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing test for no-projectRoot path\n- LOW (unfixed): `getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs, losing fidelity\n- LOW (unfixed): `createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` via spread+override without `ensureEpicTd` call\n- Coverage gap: No test for `appendToBacklogFile` append-to-existing path or error handling\n- Architecture: state.ts at 543 lines exceeds 300-line limit (pre-existing)\n\n### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — verification (2026-03-25T02:05:00Z)\n\n- AGENTS.md for src/lib was stale — missing retro-to-sprint.ts entry. Fixed.\n- Disk space critically low (45MB free) — BATS tests failed with \"No space left on device\". Cleared npm cache (2.2GB) to free space.\n- All 10 ACs passed unit-testable verification with direct CLI checks\n- Pre-existing files (state.ts at 543 lines, sprint-yaml.test.ts at 388 lines) exceed 300-line limit but were over before this story\n\n### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — create-story (2026-03-25T02:10:00Z)\n\n- Risk: selector.test.ts at 274 lines — adding ~80 lines of new tests may push past 300-line limit, conflicting with AC 9\n- Observation: Original epic had only 2 ACs; expanded to 9 to cover edge cases. Original ACs were underspecified about Tier D gate constraint.\n- Observation: Implementation is ~3 lines in sort comparator. Test changes are the bulk of work.\n\n### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:20:00Z)\n\nNo issues reported. All 11 tasks completed cleanly. 4 lines added to selector.ts, 7 test cases added via it.each. Build, vitest (3664 tests), and BATS (307 tests) all pass.\n\n### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — code-review (2026-03-25T02:27:00Z)\n\n- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md missing TD gate documentation\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Test shorthand variables polluted scope; replaced with typed it.each\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Added case-sensitivity and ready-status test cases (2 new tests, total 3666)\n- LOW (unfixed): selector.ts line 103 comment lacks Decision 6c reference\n- LOW (unfixed): keyToTitle() lowercases \"TD\" to \"Td\" — pre-existing\n- Architecture note: TD gate relies on naming convention (TD- prefix) not structured metadata — accepted tradeoff per Decision 6c\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — create-story (2026-03-25T02:42:00Z)\n\n- Risk: run.ts at 287 lines — adding Docker pre-check + orphan cleanup (~12 lines) brings it to ~299. Any additional pre-flight gates will breach 300-line limit.\n- Observation: duplicate cleanup functions — `cleanupStaleContainers()` in verify/env.ts and `cleanupContainers()` in infra/container-cleanup.ts overlap for verify containers. Harmless but is tech debt.\n- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts is a dead stub — `cleanupOrphanedContainers()` always returns 0. Real logic lives in infra module.\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:48:00Z)\n\n- Code quality concern: run.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Future additions require extracting helpers.\n- Observation: run.test.ts at 947 lines, far exceeding 300-line limit. AC#9 says no modified file exceeds 300 lines but test files routinely exceed. Followed existing pattern.\n- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts stub tests fully rewritten — implementation changed from no-op to delegation.\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — code-review (2026-03-25T02:52:00Z)\n\n- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md files for infra and commands modules were stale\n- LOW (unfixed): `isDockerAvailable()` uses `docker --version` not `docker info` — only checks CLI presence, not daemon. Pre-existing across codebase.\n- LOW (unfixed): Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again. Harmless overhead.\n- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — create-story (2026-03-25T03:05:00Z)\n\n- Risk: docker-setup.ts at 299 lines — adding backend-aware compose selection will push past 300-line limit\n- Risk: formatters.ts at 574 lines (pre-existing violation) — any additions worsen it\n- Risk: state.ts at 293 lines — adding backend field + migration pushes close to 300\n- Observation: Epic says \"ELK\" but code uses OpenSearchBackend (OpenSearch = OSS Elasticsearch fork). User-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal 'opensearch'. Documented in anti-patterns.\n- Observation: Codebase well-prepared — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, OpenSearchBackend all exist. Main gap is CLI selector and backend-aware health check dispatch.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:15:00Z)\n\n- docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Any future change requires extraction.\n- formatters.ts grew from 574 to 597 lines (pre-existing violation, grew by 23 lines). Backend-aware checks in 3 functions each needed guards.\n- Missing getElkComposeFilePath mock caused silent failure in init-project tests — fixed by adding mock and defensive writeState before Docker setup.\n- ELK compose endpoints not backend-specific — DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS still show Victoria ports even for ELK backend. Known gap, not in ACs.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — code-review (2026-03-25T03:25:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): Missing CLI validation for --observability-backend — unsafe `as` cast allows arbitrary strings\n- MEDIUM (fixed): ELK compose file resolution — 4 formatter functions resolved to Victoria compose even for ELK backend\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Wrong endpoints displayed for ELK — Victoria ports shown instead of OpenSearch ports\n- MEDIUM (fixed): resolveEndpoints() not backend-aware — always returned Victoria defaults\n- LOW (unfixed): --no-observability vs --observability-backend none have subtly different semantics\n- LOW (unfixed): formatters.ts at 605 lines — pre-existing violation, now worse\n- LOW (unfixed): docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — fragile\n- Coverage gap: No integration tests for full init --observability-backend elk CLI flow\n- Architecture: buildScopedEndpoints() uses Victoria-specific URL patterns meaningless for ELK\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:28:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon unavailable despite Docker Desktop processes running. Socket exists but not responding.\n- Waited 120+ seconds across two attempts. Infra attempt 3/10 (cumulative with prior sessions).\n- Story skipped — cannot run black-box verification without Docker.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — create-story (2026-03-25T03:32:00Z)\n\n- Observation: env.ts already over 300-line limit at 313 lines (pre-existing violation). Story guides extraction to dockerfile-generator.ts.\n- Observation: nodejs.ts at 346 lines — also over 300-line limit. Adding getVerifyDockerfileSection() will increase it further.\n- Risk: Static template deprecation — generated approach replaces them entirely. If external consumers reference templates directly, they'll break silently.\n- Ambiguity: Ubuntu 22.04 vs stack-specific base images. Architecture specifies ubuntu:22.04 but current templates use node:20-slim and rust:1.82-slim. Switching increases build time.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:41:00Z)\n\n- env.ts still at 304 lines — down from 313 but still over the 300-line NFR1 limit by 4 lines. Further extraction out of scope.\n- Static templates not deleted — kept deprecated for backward compat with older installed versions. Now dead code from main build path.\n- NodejsProvider at 358 lines — exceeds 300-line NFR1. Was 346 pre-story, added 12 lines. Pre-existing tech debt.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — socket not responding. Cannot start observability stack.\n- Retry count incremented from 3 to 4. Story remains at verifying.\n- Same infrastructure issue as prior session — Docker Desktop needs to be started manually on macOS.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — same issue as 14-4. Cannot perform black-box verification.\n- Retry count corrected: 14-5 was actually at `backlog` in sprint-state.json (yaml was stale). Reset to 0.\n\n### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — create-story (2026-03-25T03:52:00Z)\n\n- Expanded from 2 to 10 ACs covering status ownership, time budget logic, prompt cleanup, build/test gates\n- Risk: AC6 (remove state-writing from prompts) depends on finding all prompt instructions — may miss indirect ones\n- Risk: Session budget plumbing from ralph to TS orchestrator not fully specified\n- Data inconsistency found: sprint-state.json had 14-5 as `backlog` but yaml had `verifying`. Fixed both to `verifying`.\n\n### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — dev-story (2026-03-25T04:00:00Z)\n\n- Architectural mismatch: run.ts spawns a single long-running ralph process. Time budget deferral logs warnings but cannot actually kill/pause the subagent mid-phase. True phase-level control would need ralph to expose phase-change events.\n- Status ownership simplification: `story-complete` event always writes `in-review`. A phase-aware mapping would be more correct but requires knowing what phase fired the event (not in the event payload).\n- All 3729 vitest tests + 307 BATS tests pass. Build succeeds.\n\n### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — code-review (2026-03-25T04:10:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): Time budget deferral was fire-and-forget — logged but never killed the agent process. Now calls child.kill('SIGTERM').\n- HIGH (fixed): updateStoryStatus() return value silently discarded. Now logs warnings on failure.\n- MEDIUM (fixed): shouldDeferPhase returned false for NaN input (don't defer when budget unknown). Now returns true (safe default).\n- LOW (unfixed): warn import inconsistency — warnings emitted via info() with [WARN] prefix instead of using warn() helper.\n- Coverage gap: No integration test for full deferral flow (polling -> deferral -> child.kill -> clean exit).\n- Architecture: child.kill('SIGTERM') is abrupt — no graceful shutdown protocol for subagent to save progress.\n- Architecture: 5-second polling interval means up to 5s window where phase could start before deferral.\n- All 3733 tests pass. 96.97% overall coverage. All 156 files above 80% floor.\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T00:14:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `docker ps` returns \"Cannot connect to the Docker daemon\". Same issue as prior sessions.\n- All three verifying stories (14-4, 14-5, 14-6) skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→6, 14-5→1, 14-6→1.\n- Cannot fix Docker Desktop startup programmatically on macOS.\n\n### 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs — create-story (2026-03-25T00:14:30Z)\n\n- Story file already existed with full content and correct verification tags. No changes needed.\n\n### 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs — dev-story (2026-03-25T00:27:00Z)\n\n- AC3 spec mismatch: Story said \"flag-setting logic only triggers for npm test\" but coverage pipeline already handles Rust/Python/Node.js. No production code change needed — only added test to prove it works.\n- Fix 4 (ralph.sh) not unit-testable: bash changes not covered by vitest. BATS tests not added (not in scope).\n- `isBeadsCLIInstalled()` uses `which` — Unix-only, acceptable for target platform.\n- `get_current_task()` depends on jq — silently falls back to `unknown` if jq missing.\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T00:30:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `open /Applications/Docker.app` fails with error -1712 (GUI app cannot be launched from headless context).\n- All three verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→7, 14-5→2, 14-6→2.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs — code-review (2026-03-25T00:35:00Z)\n\n- No HIGH or MEDIUM bugs found.\n- LOW (unfixed): resolveStoryFilePath() uses .endsWith('.md') which breaks for gap-id appended descriptions. Pre-existing.\n- LOW (unfixed): readStoryFileStatus regex could match inside fenced code blocks. Unlikely in practice.\n- LOW (unfixed): isBeadsCLIInstalled() 5000ms timeout unnecessarily high but harmless.\n- Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor.\n- No items sent back for re-development.\n\n### 15-1-ci-file-size-gate — create-story (2026-03-25T00:42:00Z)\n\n- Observation: 11 files exceed 300 lines, 15 command files exceed 100 lines despite Epic 12 being done.\n- Risk: AC2 (zero violations) not achievable without future file-split stories. Gate set to warn mode.\n- Observation: NFR5 (commands <100 lines) has 15 violators — may warrant own epic.\n\n### 15-1-ci-file-size-gate — dev-story (2026-03-25T00:46:00Z)\n\n- AC2 intentionally unmet: gate in warn mode since 11 files still exceed 300 lines. Needs future TD stories.\n- `env -u` portability: macOS `env` doesn't support `-u` flag, used `unset` in BATS tests instead.\n- No edge case test for missing `src/commands/` directory.\n\n### 15-1-ci-file-size-gate — code-review (2026-03-25T00:49:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): .tsx files excluded from gate — ink-renderer.tsx could grow past 300 undetected\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Empty SRC_DIR=\"\" scans project root instead of src/\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Trailing slash in SRC_DIR produces double-slash in annotations\n- MEDIUM (fixed): No violation counts in output summary\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing off-by-one boundary tests (301/101 lines)\n- LOW (unfixed): find output ordering non-deterministic across platforms\n- LOW (unfixed): 2>/dev/null on NFR5 find silently swallows all errors\n- 18 BATS tests, 325 total BATS pass, 96.97% coverage\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T01:01:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `open -a Docker` fails with error -1712, `docker info` returns \"Cannot connect to Docker daemon\"\n- All three verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→9, 14-5→3, 14-6→3.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests — create-story (2026-03-25T01:04:00Z)\n\n- Epic says \"53 bare catch {} blocks\" but actual codebase has 134. Epic definition is stale.\n- AC2 already implemented — existing boundary test covers NFR4. Task 5 is verification-only.\n- ESLint // IGNORE: enforcement split across two tools (ESLint + vitest) — pragmatic workaround.\n- Risk: 134 catch block audit is mechanical but high-volume — incorrect categorizations could introduce silent bugs.\n- Risk: Barrel file re-exports may need modification for cross-module import violations.\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T01:33:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `docker ps` returns \"Cannot connect to the Docker daemon\"\n- All three verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→10 (exhausted), 14-5→4, 14-6→4.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests — code-review (2026-03-25T01:37:00Z)\n\n- No HIGH or MEDIUM issues found\n- LOW (unfixed): Boundary test blind spot — cross-module imports between protected directories not fully detected\n- LOW (unfixed): 50 ESLint warnings (unused vars) — intentionally at warn level, needs future cleanup\n- LOW (unfixed): `catch(err) {}` pattern not covered by boundary test, mitigated by ESLint no-empty rule\n- 3744 tests pass, 96.97% coverage, all 156 files above 80% floor\n\n### 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests — verification (2026-03-25T01:44:00Z)\n\n- Unit-testable verification — no Docker required\n- All 6 ACs passed with direct CLI evidence\n- Proof format required adjustment: parser needs `\\`\\`\\`bash` + `\\`\\`\\`output` pairs and `**Tier:** unit-testable` (not `**Verification tier:**`)\n- Beads sync failed (bd CLI not installed) — non-blocking\n\n### 14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T01:45:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `docker ps` returns \"Cannot connect to the Docker daemon\"\n- Both verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-5→6, 14-6→5.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 15-3-template-migration-static-files — create-story (2026-03-25T01:46:00Z)\n\n- Story file already existed with full content and correct verification tags. No creation needed.\n- Risk: Story